00:20:29.459 --> 00:20:31.250
of that is you never
have to actually store

00:20:31.250 --> 00:20:33.050
the whole matrix.

00:20:33.050 --> 00:20:35.390
You only need to evaluate
the matrix elements,

00:20:35.390 --> 00:20:36.914
and then you can
throw them away.

00:20:36.914 --> 00:20:38.580
And so if you have a
very sparse matrix,

00:20:38.580 --> 00:20:40.360
that's pretty cheap to do.

00:20:40.360 --> 00:20:42.507
So it's a really good code.

00:20:42.507 --> 00:20:44.340
I think in this 2D
problem, you can probably

00:20:44.340 --> 00:20:45.270
get away with other solvers.

00:20:45.270 --> 00:20:45.960
You don't have to use this.

00:20:45.960 --> 00:20:47.418
But this is a
definite possibility.

00:20:47.418 --> 00:20:49.560
This is a built-in
MATLAB program as well.

00:20:49.560 --> 00:20:53.310
Be warned, though, this
is an iterative solver.

00:20:53.310 --> 00:20:56.005
It's not just going
