equation any way you want.

00:38:48.860 --> 00:38:50.570
And we'll come back
to a very famous way

00:38:50.570 --> 00:38:51.611
to rewrite that equation.

00:38:51.611 --> 00:38:54.320
It's called Bayes'
theorem, and that turns out

00:38:54.320 --> 00:38:57.486
to be really important in
model versus data comparisons.

00:39:02.450 --> 00:39:07.100
Instead of doing AND, do OR.

00:39:07.100 --> 00:39:10.420
So maybe you can say, then,
what's the probability

00:39:10.420 --> 00:39:13.350
that I see at least one head?

00:39:19.240 --> 00:39:22.910
So I flip my two coins, and
I have the probability of,

00:39:22.910 --> 00:39:24.382
I see at least one head.

00:39:28.520 --> 00:39:30.935
So we know we intuitively
the answer is 3/4.

00:39:33.500 --> 00:39:36.260
