times the probability

00:41:03.900 --> 00:41:18.570
that I have head for the dime
if I had a head for the penny

00:41:18.570 --> 00:41:23.696
plus probability of
the tail for the dime

00:41:23.696 --> 00:41:30.244
or for the penny plus
the probability that I

00:41:30.244 --> 00:41:39.450
have for the dime and then
times something like this, too.

00:41:44.050 --> 00:41:46.810
And in a case like
this, where I'm summing

00:41:46.810 --> 00:41:48.070
over all of the possibilities.

00:41:48.070 --> 00:41:49.540
So in this case,
I'm either going

00:41:49.540 --> 00:41:50.740
to get a head for the dime
or a tail for the dime.

00:41:50.740 --> 00:41:52.281
It's not going to
balance on its end.

00:41:52.281 --> 00:41:54.760
I'm assuming that
