00:44:21.830 --> 00:44:25.515
Yeah, maybe-- Did I write the--

00:44:25.515 --> 00:44:27.890
I'll just write the base
theorem down the way you usually

00:44:27.890 --> 00:44:29.370
see it.

00:44:29.370 --> 00:44:31.520
So this is the
general expression,

00:44:31.520 --> 00:44:33.470
which is always true.

00:44:33.470 --> 00:44:43.970
The base theorem way to write it
is the probability of A given B

00:44:43.970 --> 00:44:53.714
is equal to the probability of
B given A times the probability

00:44:53.714 --> 00:44:59.490
of A over the probability of B.

00:44:59.490 --> 00:45:06.724
And that's just
rearranging this equality.

00:45:06.724 --> 00:45:07.390
Rearrange again.

00:45:09.970 --> 00:45:14.007
And we'll come back to
this with the situation

00:45:14.007 --> 00:45:16.090
that's like, what's the
probability that Professor

00:45:16.090 --> 00:45:20.440
Green is 5' 9", given
our measurements,

00:45:20.440 --> 00:45:23.650
is related to the probability
that if Professor Green was 5'

00:45:23.650 --> 00:45:27.300
9", we would have made
the measurements we got.

00:45:27.300 --> 00:45:30.510
So this is like that way
to invert that statement.

00:45:39.780 --> 00:45:47.355
And if the thing that's
here is exclusive,

00:45:47.355 --> 00:45:49.690
it means there's, like,
many possible things that

00:45:49.690 --> 00:45:50.934
could happen.

00:45:50.934 --> 00:45:53.240
This is the probability
that one of them happened.

00:45:53.240 --> 00:45:54.660
There's a lot of other things
that could have happened.

00:45:54.660 --> 00:45:56.090
For instance, like heads
and tails, it's either heads

00:45:56.090 --> 00:45:56.700
or it's tails.

00:45:56.700 --> 00:45:57.610
It's exclusive.

00:45:57.610 --> 00:46:06.730
If it's like that, you could
rewrite that probability of B

00:46:06.730 --> 00:46:19.150
is equal to probability of
Aj, probability of B given Aj

00:46:19.150 --> 00:46:21.940
summed over j.

00:46:21.940 --> 00:46:25.210
This is something,
whatever A measurement

00:46:25.210 --> 00:46:29.700
it is, if it ends up with
B, that's probability B.

00:46:29.700 --> 00:46:31.910
Is that all right?

00:46:31.910 --> 00:46:34.650
So you can put that into
the denominator here.

00:46:34.650 --> 00:46:36.440
You can substitute
